This paper is about developing a deep neural network for multimodal saliency detection using deep reinforcement learning. The paper focuses on computer vision and machine learning techniques, which suggests that it is likely to belong to the cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) sub-category. Additionally, the paper uses deep learning and reinforcement learning techniques, which are commonly used in the cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) sub-categories. The paper also involves decision-making and interaction with the environment, which suggests that it could belong to the cs.RO (Robotics) sub-category. Finally, the paper deals with saliency detection, which is a specific task in computer vision, and could also belong to the cs.SD (Sound and Music Computing) sub-category.
